WEBVTT

00:02.836 --> 00:04.372
Alice.
You're a woman, right?

00:04.405 --> 00:05.706
Uh-oh.

00:05.739 --> 00:07.441
So, I am in the market
for a prom date.

00:07.475 --> 00:10.111
Prom.
Wow, look at you!

00:10.144 --> 00:11.479
Anyway, when you went to prom,
what did your Prince Charming

00:11.512 --> 00:12.646
say to sweep you
off your feet?

00:12.680 --> 00:14.048
I need the exact
string of words.

00:14.082 --> 00:15.549
I actually
didn't go to prom.

00:15.583 --> 00:17.451
Oh, 'cause, like,
prom hadn't been invented yet?

00:17.485 --> 00:19.153
No.

00:19.187 --> 00:21.755
Prom just wasn't my thing.
But tons of guys asked me.

00:21.789 --> 00:24.725
Oh, great. Give me
the best of the best.

00:24.758 --> 00:26.327
This one cute guy

00:26.360 --> 00:29.263
said, "You are the single
most beautiful rose

00:29.297 --> 00:30.464
in the desert wasteland

00:30.498 --> 00:34.268
that is European History
since 1500, milady.

00:34.302 --> 00:35.769
Will you go to
prom with me?"

00:35.803 --> 00:38.472
Okay, I just recorded everything
you said with voice-to-text,

00:38.506 --> 00:41.342
I'm deleting that
boring history stuff, and send.

00:41.375 --> 00:42.643
Send?

00:42.676 --> 00:44.745
No send, Andy.

00:44.778 --> 00:46.814
You can't send it in a text,
you have to ask in person.

00:46.847 --> 00:48.416
Oh, no, that would take
way too long.

00:48.449 --> 00:50.351
Look, I just sent this
to 37 different girls

00:50.384 --> 00:51.552
in my school.

00:51.585 --> 00:53.121
You know.
Gonna cast a wide net.

00:53.154 --> 00:53.921
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

00:53.954 --> 00:56.857
Looks like we have...
our first no.

00:56.890 --> 00:58.559
Well,
it's a numbers game.

00:58.592 --> 01:00.261
I'm not worried.

01:00.294 --> 01:02.263
[ Cellphone vibrating ]
"No." "No."

01:02.296 --> 01:03.631
"Unsubscribe"?
Mm.

01:03.664 --> 01:05.333
Well, at least
they're replying to me

01:05.366 --> 01:07.168
in a timely fashion.

01:07.201 --> 01:08.202
And in all caps.

01:08.236 --> 01:09.637
Andy...
[ Doorbell rings ]

01:09.670 --> 01:11.605
Yay!
Strangers at the door!

01:11.639 --> 01:13.374
I got it!

01:13.407 --> 01:14.408
Is Dora home?

01:14.442 --> 01:15.676
Dora!

01:15.709 --> 01:18.412
Some dork
is at the door!

01:18.446 --> 01:20.648
Oops, I forgot to use
my inside voice.

01:21.582 --> 01:23.083
Gabe?

01:24.152 --> 01:25.653
Oh, crap.

01:25.686 --> 01:28.356
Three, four.

01:28.389 --> 01:29.657
* Hold on, little girl

01:29.690 --> 01:32.560
* Show me
what he's done to you *

01:32.593 --> 01:35.696
* Stand up, little girl

01:35.729 --> 01:38.232
* A broken heart
can't be that bad *

01:38.266 --> 01:39.500
What the hell
is happening?

01:39.533 --> 01:41.335
It's so adorable.

01:41.369 --> 01:44.238
Dora's being asked to the prom
by some dude named Gabe.

01:44.272 --> 01:47.241
* So come on, baby,
come on over *

01:47.275 --> 01:50.544
* Let me be the one
to show you *

01:50.578 --> 01:52.713
* I'm the one
who wants to go *

01:52.746 --> 01:55.616
* To prom with you

01:55.649 --> 01:56.850
Oh.
[ Chuckles ]

01:56.884 --> 01:58.486
Poor, stupid Gabe.

01:58.519 --> 02:01.522
* I know
you feel it, too *

02:01.555 --> 02:02.923
Yeah, I'm gonna
stop you right there.

02:02.956 --> 02:04.325
Uh, I don't
feel it, too.

02:04.358 --> 02:05.626
Prom's not really
my thing.

02:05.659 --> 02:09.263
I guess what I'm trying
to say is...

02:10.331 --> 02:12.300
Thank you
for the opportunity.

02:12.333 --> 02:13.301
Dora: Anytime!

02:13.334 --> 02:14.335
Sorry.

02:14.368 --> 02:17.238
She said no.

02:17.271 --> 02:18.439
Mary:
This is Alice.

02:18.472 --> 02:20.841
When she was a kid, she dreamed
up me to be her bff.

02:20.874 --> 02:23.611
Now my girl
has finally fallen in love,

02:23.644 --> 02:26.247
but she's in way over her head,
so I'm back to help.

02:26.280 --> 02:27.915
I've got this
all figured out.

02:27.948 --> 02:29.650
No, you don't.
No, I don't.

02:29.683 --> 02:31.252
-- Captions by VITAC --

02:31.285 --> 02:33.687
I cannot believe
Dora said no

02:33.721 --> 02:35.523
to that adorable
prom proposal.

02:35.556 --> 02:37.858
The old wound
is reopened now.

02:37.891 --> 02:40.394
I should've gone to prom.
It's my biggest regret.

02:40.428 --> 02:41.862
That's your
biggest regret?

02:41.895 --> 02:44.532
I've seen you eat a hot dog
you dropped in the subway.

02:44.565 --> 02:46.234
I've seen you
punch a bird.

02:46.267 --> 02:48.402
I didn't punch the bird,
the bird flew at my face

02:48.436 --> 02:49.737
and I gently shooed it
to the ground.

02:49.770 --> 02:51.505
This is gently shooing.

02:51.539 --> 02:53.574
This -- Ah! --
is a bird slap.

02:53.607 --> 02:55.409
But whatever.
You should talk to Dora.

02:55.443 --> 02:56.877
I'm gonna go
talk to Dora.

02:56.910 --> 02:59.580
So no one asked you to prom
because you punched a bird?

02:59.613 --> 03:02.483
No, people thought I punched
the bird, but that's not...

03:02.516 --> 03:03.784
my main point.

03:03.817 --> 03:05.886
[ Sighs ]

03:05.919 --> 03:07.555
I always
got asked to prom,

03:07.588 --> 03:10.591
and I always said no,
and then in my senior year,

03:10.624 --> 03:12.993
when I actually wanted to go,
no one asked.

03:13.026 --> 03:14.228
Okay.

03:14.262 --> 03:16.630
Maybe prom was cool back in
your day when it was invented...

03:16.664 --> 03:18.499
How old do you guys
think I am?

03:18.532 --> 03:20.601
Point is,
prom is lame.

03:20.634 --> 03:22.703
All the dressing up,
the popular music,

03:22.736 --> 03:24.505
the outdated
gender norms.

03:24.538 --> 03:26.740
Prom's never, like,
like, cool.

03:26.774 --> 03:28.276
Like in the movie
"Carrie."

03:28.309 --> 03:30.878
Every now and then,

03:30.911 --> 03:32.780
pop music
and outdated gender norms

03:32.813 --> 03:34.248
can be fun, Dora.

03:34.282 --> 03:35.549
I don't know.

03:35.583 --> 03:37.585
Plus, I thought Gabe's
prom-posal was pretty brave.

03:37.618 --> 03:39.687
Yeah, it does take
a certain amount of courage

03:39.720 --> 03:40.588
to look like an idiot.

03:40.621 --> 03:41.922
There is something

03:41.955 --> 03:44.958
kind of, like, mysterious
about trombonists.

03:44.992 --> 03:46.927
Sure.

03:46.960 --> 03:48.662
[ Chuckles ]

03:53.033 --> 03:55.536
Is Dora here?
Oh, bro.

03:55.569 --> 03:56.670
Bro, bro, bro.

03:56.704 --> 03:58.005
Dad, I got this.

04:00.708 --> 04:01.675
Three, four.

04:01.709 --> 04:03.744
* Will you go to prom

04:03.777 --> 04:06.480
* With Gabe Bernstein?

04:06.514 --> 04:08.282
* He is quite respectful

04:08.316 --> 04:10.584
It's happening again?

04:10.618 --> 04:11.952
* For a teen
All right, guys.

04:11.985 --> 04:12.953
Please.
I'm saying yes.

04:12.986 --> 04:14.288
Don't make me
change my mind.

04:14.322 --> 04:15.656
Yes!
[ Gasps ]

04:15.689 --> 04:17.291
Thanks, Dora.
I'm so excited.

04:17.325 --> 04:18.859
You sure are.

04:18.892 --> 04:20.461
Bye.

04:20.494 --> 04:21.462
Yes!

04:21.495 --> 04:22.796
Whoa, whoa.
What was that?

04:22.830 --> 04:24.432
I thought prom
wasn't your thing.

04:24.465 --> 04:26.500
It's not, but Alice
kind of freaked me out,

04:26.534 --> 04:27.735
and I don't want
to end up like her.

04:27.768 --> 04:30.604
That is so insulting
and you took my advice!

04:30.638 --> 04:32.473
[ Grunts ]
Can we do prom pictures here?

04:32.506 --> 04:33.907
Ben, can we do
prom pictures here?

04:33.941 --> 04:36.444
No.
I-I'm sorry, okay?

04:36.477 --> 04:37.778
It's just that...

04:37.811 --> 04:38.712
Dora can't go.

04:38.746 --> 04:39.880
What?
What?

04:39.913 --> 04:41.315
Look, you're Andy's
little sister.

04:41.349 --> 04:42.650
You can't
go to prom before him.

04:42.683 --> 04:43.951
It'll send him
off the deep end.

04:43.984 --> 04:45.085
Oh.

04:45.118 --> 04:46.687
That's why
we have the Andy Rule --

04:46.720 --> 04:48.322
You can't achieve
milestones before him.

04:48.356 --> 04:49.623
It's not worth it.

04:49.657 --> 04:50.724
You could've
said something

04:50.758 --> 04:52.025
before I told Gabe
to ask me again.

04:52.059 --> 04:54.695
You were so insistent that prom
was for suck-ass douche lords

04:54.728 --> 04:55.796
that I didn't think
I had to.

04:55.829 --> 04:57.665
So if Andy gets a date,
then I can go?

04:57.698 --> 04:58.666
Absolutely.

04:58.699 --> 05:00.468
So it's not happening.

05:00.501 --> 05:02.470
Hopefully,
Gabe will understand.

05:03.737 --> 05:04.972
Oh, poor kid.

05:05.005 --> 05:07.608
Poor kid?
Poor me.

05:07.641 --> 05:08.976
You almost blew it!

05:09.009 --> 05:10.978
All your prom talk
almost got inside Dora's head.

05:11.011 --> 05:12.713
Wait,
what are you saying?

05:12.746 --> 05:14.382
I'm saying I don't want
Dora to go to prom

05:14.415 --> 05:15.716
because she's
my little baby Princess.

05:15.749 --> 05:17.685
So you're hiding
behind Andy's lack of game

05:17.718 --> 05:20.721
to keep Dora from taking part
in a rite of passage?

05:20.754 --> 05:22.490
No, it's not like that.

05:22.523 --> 05:24.758
Prom is just different for boys.
You get it.

05:24.792 --> 05:27.428
Yeah, I get it.
It's called a double standard.

05:27.461 --> 05:29.029
No, it's two single
and equal standards

05:29.062 --> 05:30.864
that I choose
to measure differently.

05:33.734 --> 05:34.535
Oh, God!

05:34.568 --> 05:36.804
Sorry, just mixing
up my entrances.

05:36.837 --> 05:38.872
We're totally calling him out
on this double standard garbagio

05:38.906 --> 05:40.107
and getting Andy
a date, right?

05:40.140 --> 05:41.509
Oh, hell, yeah.

05:41.542 --> 05:43.010
Slipping, slipping!
Ah!

05:43.043 --> 05:45.045
Hey, champ.

05:45.078 --> 05:46.614
How's it going
on the prom front?

05:46.647 --> 05:48.416
It's good.
I've still got tons of options.

05:48.449 --> 05:49.650
I'm down to four girls.

05:49.683 --> 05:51.919
[ Cellphone vibrates ]
Three girls.

05:51.952 --> 05:54.488
You didn't even look.
Eh. Didn't have to.
There's been a theme.

05:54.522 --> 05:56.023
Okay.

05:56.056 --> 05:58.426
So, clearly mass-texting
your entire class

05:58.459 --> 05:59.727
was not the way to go.

05:59.760 --> 06:01.629
Well, I didn't
text everybody.

06:01.662 --> 06:03.764
I can work with that.

06:03.797 --> 06:05.766
Gonna call out
some lady names here.

06:05.799 --> 06:08.135
And they're all
crossed out.

06:08.168 --> 06:09.737
Laura Wadler.

06:09.770 --> 06:11.004
Boom.
How about her?

06:11.038 --> 06:12.005
She starts fires.

06:12.039 --> 06:13.040
Okay.

06:13.073 --> 06:14.875
Denise Bagley.

06:14.908 --> 06:16.009
She's super nice and cute.
Uh-huh?

06:16.043 --> 06:18.011
But she's going
with Jennifer Gomez.

06:18.045 --> 06:19.547
To elaborate,
they're lovers.

06:19.580 --> 06:20.881
[ Clicks tongue ]
Gotcha. [ Gasps ]

06:20.914 --> 06:22.616
Aww, Clara Chang.

06:22.650 --> 06:23.884
Wasn't she in Dora's play
with you?

06:23.917 --> 06:25.719
You guys
are so cute together.

06:25.753 --> 06:27.921
Man, I...
I can't ask her.

06:27.955 --> 06:29.189
I like her and stuff.

06:29.222 --> 06:31.525
Wait.
You actually like her?

06:31.559 --> 06:33.527
Well, it's more like love.
[ Chuckles ]

06:33.561 --> 06:36.029
Dude! Why didn't you just
ask her in the first place?

06:36.063 --> 06:37.931
A-Again,
because I love her.

06:37.965 --> 06:39.933
I mean, what if
she says no to me?

06:39.967 --> 06:41.769
That would actually
hurt my feelings.

06:41.802 --> 06:44.204
Andy, you're just trying
to protect your little heart.

06:44.237 --> 06:46.173
Oh, actually,
the doctor says it's enlarged.

06:46.206 --> 06:47.808
But yeah.

06:47.841 --> 06:49.643
One no from Clara,
that -- that would --

06:49.677 --> 06:50.944
that would be worse
than a thousand nos

06:50.978 --> 06:52.212
from all these girls.

06:52.245 --> 06:54.915
Andy, you just got
to take a chance.

06:54.948 --> 06:56.517
I mean, look at
me and your dad.

06:56.550 --> 06:57.451
If he hadn't sacked up

06:57.485 --> 06:59.052
and asked me out,
we wouldn't be here now.

06:59.086 --> 07:01.489
You're right. You're totally
out of my dad's league.

07:01.522 --> 07:02.590
I am.

07:02.623 --> 07:04.792
Okay.
I'm gonna ask Clara.

07:04.825 --> 07:05.793
Okay.

07:05.826 --> 07:07.895
[ Clears throat ]

07:07.928 --> 07:08.929
"Prom,"
question mark...

07:08.962 --> 07:10.964
No, no.
Don't text her.

07:10.998 --> 07:12.666
Oh, no.

07:12.700 --> 07:13.934
Oh, I-I-I just sent it,

07:13.967 --> 07:16.970
and autocorrect changed it
from "prom" to "porn."

07:17.004 --> 07:19.640
What?
Why did it do that?

07:19.673 --> 07:20.941
I don't know!
I've never once

07:20.974 --> 07:22.943
typed in that word before!
Why would I?!

07:22.976 --> 07:24.111
Clearly,
I've been hacked.

07:24.144 --> 07:26.814
I've been hacked by a gross,
shameful,

07:26.847 --> 07:28.181
naturally curious person.

07:28.215 --> 07:30.918
Let's just move on.

07:30.951 --> 07:32.986
We will start
by letting go of this.

07:33.020 --> 07:35.188
We are going to ask Clara
the right way,

07:35.222 --> 07:36.857
with a big
romantic display,

07:36.890 --> 07:38.792
just like all the kids
are doing now.

07:38.826 --> 07:40.861
Okay. Yeah, I'm in.

07:40.894 --> 07:42.129
Okay.
What do I do?

07:42.162 --> 07:44.164
Oh, God.

07:44.197 --> 07:45.833
I'm about to
ask out Clara.

07:45.866 --> 07:47.735
Is that right?
It feels weird in my mouth.

07:47.768 --> 07:49.703
Andy, relax.
This is the cutest prom-posal

07:49.737 --> 07:51.171
your school
has ever seen.

07:51.204 --> 07:53.941
Yeah, okay.
Here goes nothing.

07:53.974 --> 07:55.976
Uh, uh...

08:00.914 --> 08:02.783
[ Gasps ] Oh, no.

08:02.816 --> 08:04.552
Why'd you
throw a rock?!

08:04.585 --> 08:05.619
There were no pebbles!

08:05.653 --> 08:07.588
What about the doorbell?

08:07.621 --> 08:09.623
How am I supposed to hit
the doorbell with a rock?!

08:09.657 --> 08:10.824
Alice, come on!

08:10.858 --> 08:12.626
[ Gasps ]

08:12.660 --> 08:15.863
No. No, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no!

08:15.896 --> 08:17.130
Oh, please,
don't -- stop!

08:17.164 --> 08:18.632
This can't
be happening!

08:18.666 --> 08:19.867
If you were gonna do it,
at least finish your job!

08:19.900 --> 08:21.802
Come back, please!

08:21.835 --> 08:23.571
Sir!
Clara: Andy?

08:23.604 --> 08:25.305
What's happening?

08:25.338 --> 08:27.975
[ Chuckles ]
It's a funny story.

08:28.008 --> 08:31.612
**

08:31.645 --> 08:32.780
Excuse me.

08:32.813 --> 08:35.015
**

08:38.251 --> 08:40.888
Oh, God, oh, God, oh, God.
This is a disaster and I have

08:40.921 --> 08:42.556
math class first period.
What do I even say to her?

08:42.590 --> 08:43.991
Nothing,
you ditch math -- no.

08:44.024 --> 08:45.993
I'm an adult.
I cannot suggest that.

08:46.026 --> 08:48.161
Oh, no,
she's walking over.

08:48.195 --> 08:49.930
Drive, drive, drive, drive!
Why aren't you driving?!

08:49.963 --> 08:51.732
We can't run away.
You have to talk to her.

08:51.765 --> 08:53.266
Never.

08:53.300 --> 08:55.202
Oh, sweet Lord,
she's knocking on the window.

08:55.235 --> 08:57.004
Andy?
And she's saying my name.

08:57.037 --> 08:58.171
She knows it's me.

08:58.205 --> 08:59.640
I can hear you.

08:59.673 --> 09:01.174
I'm rolling the
window down now.

09:01.208 --> 09:03.176
Don't you dare.
I will never forgive you.

09:03.210 --> 09:06.113
Hey, Clara.
What's shakin', bacon?

09:06.146 --> 09:07.981
Well, you texted me
the word "porn,"

09:08.015 --> 09:09.817
then broke my window,

09:09.850 --> 09:11.785
and also wrote,
"Clara, do me," on the street.

09:11.819 --> 09:13.020
Hmm. Well, someone's
full of herself.

09:13.053 --> 09:16.089
So...are you asking me
to prom or what?

09:16.123 --> 09:17.758
Uh, uh...

09:17.791 --> 09:20.093
Yes, he's asking
you to prom.

09:20.127 --> 09:21.929
Cool. Uh, e-mail me
the deets,

09:21.962 --> 09:24.064
and I'll hit you back with
the bill for my bedroom window.

09:24.097 --> 09:25.332
My parents are irate.

09:27.167 --> 09:30.270
[ Both yelling ]

09:30.303 --> 09:32.973
I just asked Clara to prom
using you as a proxy!

09:33.006 --> 09:34.241
I am the man!

09:34.274 --> 09:35.375
You really are!
Yeah!

09:35.408 --> 09:37.144
This is how we do!
This is how we --

09:37.177 --> 09:38.378
[ Gasps ]

09:38.411 --> 09:41.214
Thank you
for your help with this.

09:43.316 --> 09:45.653
Son of a bitch.

09:46.720 --> 09:47.988
Hi, Mr. Cooper.
Is Dora --

09:48.021 --> 09:50.223
Dora home? I know.

09:50.257 --> 09:52.292
Bro, why are you
doing this?

09:52.325 --> 09:54.094
Oh.

09:56.797 --> 09:58.031
* This is the last time...

09:58.065 --> 10:00.100
A third time?
So exciting.

10:00.133 --> 10:02.069
* I'm gonna ask

10:02.102 --> 10:04.171
* Will you go to prom

10:04.204 --> 10:06.239
* With Gabe at last?

10:06.273 --> 10:07.775
* Gabe, at last

10:07.808 --> 10:09.877
* It's just like a scene

10:09.910 --> 10:12.045
* From a rom-com

10:12.079 --> 10:13.246
* From a rom-com

10:13.280 --> 10:15.182
* We'll go to Olive Garden

10:15.215 --> 10:18.418
* And then hit prom

10:18.451 --> 10:21.188
* No bottom to

10:21.221 --> 10:22.956
* The breadsticks

10:22.990 --> 10:24.191
[ Chuckles ]

10:24.224 --> 10:26.059
Uh, why all this?

10:26.093 --> 10:28.028
I-I already texted you
we were back on.

10:28.061 --> 10:30.263
I know, but I wanted
to do it right.

10:30.297 --> 10:32.099
You deserve the big ask.

10:33.834 --> 10:35.335
Aww.
[ Groans ]

10:35.368 --> 10:39.206
Well, uh, I'll admit
the song is growing on me.

10:39.239 --> 10:40.273
So, still yes.

10:40.307 --> 10:42.375
Great.
I'm looking forward to it.

10:42.409 --> 10:44.444
Okay. [ Chuckles ]
Bye.

10:44.477 --> 10:47.047
Okay. [ Chuckles ]
Bye.

10:47.080 --> 10:49.683
Okay. Bye.
[ Chuckles ]

10:49.717 --> 10:51.852
Okay, bye.

10:51.885 --> 10:53.954
She said yes.

10:53.987 --> 10:55.222
Again!
[ Cheering ]

10:55.255 --> 10:56.356
Dora,
we talked about this.

10:56.389 --> 10:58.191
You can't go unless you-know-who
gets a you-know-what,

10:58.225 --> 11:00.093
which will happen when
you-know-where freezes over.

11:00.127 --> 11:02.462
You didn't hear?

11:02.495 --> 11:04.832
Andy, tell dad
the good news.

11:04.865 --> 11:07.901
You have to pay $358
for a broken window.

11:07.935 --> 11:09.069
What?

11:09.102 --> 11:11.371
And I got
a date to prom.

11:11.404 --> 11:13.741
I got a date
to prom.
No.

11:13.774 --> 11:15.142
Yeah.
No.

11:15.175 --> 11:16.409
Yeah.
No way.

11:16.443 --> 11:17.978
Yes.
No.

11:18.011 --> 11:19.079
Yes!

11:19.112 --> 11:20.080
All thanks to Alice.

11:20.113 --> 11:21.048
She literally
asked for me.

11:21.081 --> 11:22.950
I mean, she said
the words and everything.

11:22.983 --> 11:26.253
Alice,
you are the best.

11:26.286 --> 11:27.921
Now I get to go
to prom!

11:27.955 --> 11:31.158
Good thing you clearly laid out
those super specific rules.

11:31.191 --> 11:33.393
You are
the best, Alice.

11:37.464 --> 11:40.000
Okay, I know this is not
what you intended,

11:40.033 --> 11:43.003
but this
is a very big moment!

11:43.036 --> 11:44.204
Dora took my advice;

11:44.237 --> 11:47.307
Andy, thanks to me, gets a date
with the girl he loves.

11:47.340 --> 11:49.843
I mean, this is great!
Right?

11:49.877 --> 11:51.178
Mm.
Ooh. [ Groans ]

11:53.914 --> 11:55.115
[ Sighs ]

11:55.148 --> 11:57.350
Oh, damn,
he is pissed!

11:57.384 --> 11:59.186
Do you think
I went too far helping Andy?

11:59.219 --> 12:01.288
Hell, No.
One -- the guy is wrong.

12:01.321 --> 12:03.824
Two -- If Ben wants you to get
involved in the kids' lives,

12:03.857 --> 12:04.892
he's got to know

12:04.925 --> 12:06.493
you're gonna bring
your own flavor.

12:06.526 --> 12:09.129
All day.
Flavor's my middle name.

12:09.162 --> 12:10.497
No, it's not.
It's Lurleen.

12:10.530 --> 12:13.133
Shut up.

12:13.166 --> 12:14.234
**

12:14.267 --> 12:16.236
Okay,
you're super angry.

12:16.269 --> 12:17.971
[ Scoffs ]
Me? What makes you say that?

12:18.005 --> 12:20.207
Well, maybe because
you stormed out, and now

12:20.240 --> 12:22.242
you're furiously slathering mayo
on what's shaping up

12:22.275 --> 12:23.376
to be a multi-decker
hate sandwich.

12:23.410 --> 12:25.178
Well, it's just,
I told you I didn't want

12:25.212 --> 12:27.414
Dora to go to prom,
and you forced it to happen.

12:27.447 --> 12:30.317
I'm sorry, it's just I know
what it's like to miss out,

12:30.350 --> 12:32.052
and I don't want Dora
to go through that.

12:32.085 --> 12:33.921
Did you hear her
with that Gabe?

12:33.954 --> 12:36.189
[ As Dora ]
"Okay, bye. Okay, bye."

12:36.223 --> 12:37.825
You know what
I heard?

12:37.858 --> 12:40.160
"Okay, bye, innocence.
Okay, bye, virginity."

12:40.193 --> 12:43.263
You're overreacting.
It's just a school dance.

12:43.296 --> 12:45.899
Prom is a gateway dance.
Ben...

12:45.933 --> 12:48.335
She's growing up, and it's scary
and overwhelming and sad,

12:48.368 --> 12:49.402
and pass me
the pickle chips.

12:52.539 --> 12:53.974
[ Pickles plop ]
Honey,

12:54.007 --> 12:55.809
honey,
I promise you,

12:55.843 --> 12:57.377
when you see Dora
walk down those stairs

12:57.410 --> 12:58.879
wearing a beautiful gown,

12:58.912 --> 13:00.513
all of your fear and anger
will melt away,

13:00.547 --> 13:03.316
and you'll just be left
with super happy dad feels.

13:03.350 --> 13:05.552
Whatever, fine. Everybody
can just do what they want,

13:05.585 --> 13:08.055
because I've obviously
lost control of this family.

13:08.088 --> 13:10.223
The only thing I can control
is this sandwich.

13:12.225 --> 13:13.493
Damn it!

13:13.526 --> 13:15.262
Okay, Andy,
put your arm around Clara.

13:15.295 --> 13:17.397
Here goes everything.

13:20.400 --> 13:21.201
Andy,
lose the hover hand.

13:21.234 --> 13:22.535
The what?

13:22.569 --> 13:24.471
Well, your hand's
just floating high above her.

13:24.504 --> 13:26.106
It's okay, you can
touch my shoulder.

13:26.139 --> 13:27.908
But it's so bare
and well-moisturized.

13:27.941 --> 13:30.878
Look, I like you, dude.
You're not like the other guys.

13:30.911 --> 13:32.545
You're kind of
an oddball.

13:32.579 --> 13:34.014
Thank you.

13:34.047 --> 13:35.415
So...

13:40.387 --> 13:42.389
Damn!
Looking sharp, kiddo.

13:42.422 --> 13:43.823
Dora:
Coming down.

13:45.125 --> 13:48.428
**

13:54.301 --> 13:56.536
Oh, [bleep] no.
[ Music warps and fades ]

13:56.569 --> 13:57.637
What dat?

13:57.670 --> 13:59.072
Nothing.

14:00.273 --> 14:02.009
Dora,
you look...

14:02.042 --> 14:03.343
Wow.

14:03.376 --> 14:04.978
Ben:
Yes, "wow."

14:05.012 --> 14:06.279
You look
so great, honey.

14:06.313 --> 14:09.516
Really, so adult.
Adults only.

14:09.549 --> 14:10.617
You okay, Ben?

14:10.650 --> 14:11.651
Yes!

14:11.684 --> 14:14.521
Big stuff.
Hey, Gabe,

14:14.554 --> 14:16.389
your boutonniere's slipping.
Let me get that for ya.

14:16.423 --> 14:18.125
Is it?
Uh, yes, it is.

14:18.158 --> 14:19.392
Excuse us.

14:21.328 --> 14:23.063
Ooh, sharp.

14:23.096 --> 14:25.999
Uh, you know, I could probably
pin that on myself.

14:26.033 --> 14:28.168
Let me tell you
something, Gabe.

14:28.201 --> 14:30.437
I have a very particular
set of skills,

14:30.470 --> 14:33.273
skills that I have acquired
over a very long career,

14:33.306 --> 14:35.976
skills that make me a nightmare
for people like you.

14:36.009 --> 14:39.346
Um, isn't that the Liam Neeson
speech from the movie "Taken"?

14:39.379 --> 14:41.381
Ooh.

14:41.414 --> 14:43.483
Look who watches
PG-13 movies.

14:43.516 --> 14:44.517
Um...

14:44.551 --> 14:45.618
Follow me, Gabe.

14:45.652 --> 14:47.554
Okay.

14:47.587 --> 14:49.689
You'll have my daughter
returned home safe,

14:49.722 --> 14:51.258
and that'll be
the end of it, Gabe.

14:51.291 --> 14:53.560
I will not look for you.
I will not pursue you.

14:53.593 --> 14:57.364
But if you break curfew
or her heart,

14:57.397 --> 15:01.134
I will look for you.

15:01.168 --> 15:04.071
I will find you.

15:04.104 --> 15:05.438
And I will kill you.

15:07.174 --> 15:08.441
[ Both laugh ]

15:08.475 --> 15:11.044
It's a great movie,
huh?

15:11.078 --> 15:12.112
Love that line.

15:12.145 --> 15:13.546
Anywho,
have fun tonight.

15:13.580 --> 15:14.547
Yay!

15:14.581 --> 15:15.983
Okay,
one last group shot.

15:16.016 --> 15:17.117
Dora,
where's Gabe?

15:17.150 --> 15:19.486
Um, don't know.

15:19.519 --> 15:20.720
He said he was going
to the bathroom.

15:20.753 --> 15:22.289
The downstairs bathroom?

15:22.322 --> 15:23.390
'Cause I was just in there
and the window was open,

15:23.423 --> 15:25.292
and the curtains were blowing.
[ Cellphone chimes ]

15:25.325 --> 15:26.559
Oh, my God.

15:26.593 --> 15:28.261
Gabe just ditched me.

15:28.295 --> 15:29.262
Oh, no.
What?

15:29.296 --> 15:31.965
Dad, what did you say
to Gabe?

15:31.999 --> 15:33.466
What? Nothing.

15:33.500 --> 15:35.168
'Cause this text says

15:35.202 --> 15:37.104
that in the interest
of his personal safety,

15:37.137 --> 15:38.972
he thinks it's best
if we never speak again.

15:39.006 --> 15:41.041
[ Scoffs ]
Classic Gabe.

15:41.074 --> 15:42.475
Always freaking out
for no reason.

15:42.509 --> 15:45.478
[ Cellphone chimes ]

15:45.512 --> 15:47.981
Alice: "To be absolutely clear,
I think you're great,

15:48.015 --> 15:49.482
and the only
reason I ran

15:49.516 --> 15:51.584
is 'cause your father
threatened to take my life."

15:51.618 --> 15:53.386
How could you do this
to me?

15:53.420 --> 15:55.288
'Cause I didn't want you
to go to prom.

15:55.322 --> 15:56.656
What about Andy?

15:56.689 --> 15:59.292
Well, i-it's different
with boys.

15:59.326 --> 16:02.729
Dad, that's a full-on
double standard against girls.

16:02.762 --> 16:04.231
Oh, my God!

16:04.264 --> 16:06.233
You tried to trick me
with the Andy Rule.

16:06.266 --> 16:08.068
Uh, hi, I'm --
I'm Andy.

16:08.101 --> 16:10.203
Feeling like I deserve
to know the Andy rule.

16:10.237 --> 16:12.472
No, she said,
"Andy rules." Go, Andy.

16:12.505 --> 16:13.540
Dad said I couldn't

16:13.573 --> 16:15.275
go to prom
unless you got a date,

16:15.308 --> 16:17.377
which he thought
would never happen.

16:17.410 --> 16:18.711
Andy:
Well, guess what.

16:18.745 --> 16:21.614
Now I am standing here
with my arm around --

16:21.648 --> 16:23.450
That's right,
all the way around --

16:23.483 --> 16:25.485
This lovely angel,
proving you wrong.

16:25.518 --> 16:28.721
Let's just go stand somewhere
near the street.

16:29.789 --> 16:31.324
[ Door opens ]

16:31.358 --> 16:33.493
I know I act all tough
and above it all...

16:33.526 --> 16:37.297
but -- but the truth is
I really wanted to go to prom.

16:37.330 --> 16:38.431
Thanks a lot.

16:38.465 --> 16:41.501
**

16:45.738 --> 16:48.175
Dora,
I'm sorry.

16:48.208 --> 16:49.576
Please come out,
Princess.

16:49.609 --> 16:51.144
Dora: [ Crying ]
I'm not your princess.

16:51.178 --> 16:54.081
I'm a grown-Ass woman.
Just come out.

16:54.114 --> 16:56.116
We-We can make milkshakes
and watch "Care Bears."

16:56.149 --> 16:57.484
"Care Bears"?

16:57.517 --> 17:00.053
I don't want
"Care Bears."

17:00.087 --> 17:01.321
I want Gabe.

17:01.354 --> 17:02.522
I love him.

17:02.555 --> 17:04.591
All right, come on.
It's true.

17:04.624 --> 17:06.826
I love everything
about Gabe Saperstein.

17:06.859 --> 17:08.461
I think
it's Bernstein.

17:08.495 --> 17:09.596
Well, whatever.

17:09.629 --> 17:13.800
I love how he's sweet
and -- and an average height.

17:13.833 --> 17:16.169
I love how he comes
and sings at doors.

17:16.203 --> 17:19.639
And I love...[ Sobs ]

17:19.672 --> 17:21.208
...how his name
is Gabe.

17:21.241 --> 17:23.510
Yes, you clearly know
all about him.

17:23.543 --> 17:26.513
Well, I know you can't
keep us apart!

17:26.546 --> 17:27.614
I long for him.

17:27.647 --> 17:29.116
You long for no boy!

17:29.149 --> 17:31.251
The more you tell me
I can't long for him,

17:31.284 --> 17:32.519
the longer
my longing becomes.

17:32.552 --> 17:34.387
Okay, let's take it easy,
everybody.

17:34.421 --> 17:35.522
What's the difference?

17:35.555 --> 17:37.357
Dad got
what he wanted.

17:37.390 --> 17:38.825
I'm not
going to prom.

17:38.858 --> 17:40.193
I guess I'm the
kind of princess

17:40.227 --> 17:42.162
who gets locked up
in a tower!

17:42.195 --> 17:44.497
**

17:47.367 --> 17:49.269
Be honest.
I'm horrible, right?

17:49.302 --> 17:51.538
Eh...

17:51.571 --> 17:53.106
Y-You're just
making a noise.

17:53.140 --> 17:54.441
Is it a good noise?

17:54.474 --> 17:56.876
Eh...

17:56.909 --> 17:59.312
Yeah,
I deserved that.

18:00.880 --> 18:03.716
It's hard for dads when
their little girls grow up.

18:03.750 --> 18:05.285
She used to be
my little pumpkin

18:05.318 --> 18:07.254
who'd run into my arms
when I came home

18:07.287 --> 18:10.290
or ask me
to kiss her ouchies.

18:10.323 --> 18:12.692
She's gone.
It's all gone.

18:12.725 --> 18:15.428
Yeah, but now she's this
amazing young woman

18:15.462 --> 18:17.764
who's special
in a whole new way.

18:17.797 --> 18:19.599
Yeah,
but that's the thing.

18:19.632 --> 18:21.268
She's gonna disappear, too.

18:21.301 --> 18:23.270
[ Chuckles ]

18:23.303 --> 18:25.705
I guess I thought
if I could hold off on prom

18:25.738 --> 18:28.175
for just another year,
then, I don't know,

18:28.208 --> 18:29.776
maybe I could
slow things down.

18:29.809 --> 18:30.910
Yeah,
but you can't.

18:30.943 --> 18:35.148
Yeah. I know.

18:35.182 --> 18:36.716
So what now?

18:36.749 --> 18:38.151
Go to her.

18:38.185 --> 18:40.187
And tell her
to go to him.

18:40.220 --> 18:41.788
To get him to go
with her to the prom.

18:41.821 --> 18:42.789
Yeah, no, no,
I got it.

18:42.822 --> 18:44.391
Okay.
Thank you.

18:46.759 --> 18:48.161
Hey.

18:48.195 --> 18:49.396
Hey.

18:50.763 --> 18:51.898
"Taken" dad!

18:51.931 --> 18:53.633
No, no, no, no, no.
We're cool.

18:54.767 --> 18:56.469
So sorry about before.

18:56.503 --> 18:58.238
I got
totally carried away.

18:58.271 --> 19:00.240
Gabe,
you're a sweet boy.

19:00.273 --> 19:01.274
Dora,
take it away.

19:01.308 --> 19:05.378
Gabe, I owe you
an apology, too.

19:05.412 --> 19:07.847
I should've just said yes
the first time you asked.

19:07.880 --> 19:09.716
[ Inhales sharply ]
Ah, that's why I'm here.

19:09.749 --> 19:10.817
Um...[ Laughs ]

19:10.850 --> 19:13.820
N-Not just -- Not just
'cause I want to go to prom,

19:13.853 --> 19:17.457
but because I want to go
to prom with you.

19:19.359 --> 19:20.627
Two, three, four.

19:20.660 --> 19:25.532
* Sorry I was such
a jerk before *

19:25.565 --> 19:29.302
* I want to go to prom,
get in the car *

19:30.570 --> 19:34.241
* Oops, that sounded
kind of threatening *

19:35.408 --> 19:36.843
[ Laughs ]
Sorry, this is weird.

19:36.876 --> 19:40.380
* I'm not good
at these things *

19:43.316 --> 19:45.618
[ Laughs ]

19:45.652 --> 19:48.355
I know half these kids
are probably on Molly,

19:48.388 --> 19:50.690
but it's so cute.

19:50.723 --> 19:53.360
Ben:
Got to admit,

19:53.393 --> 19:55.762
having some
super happy dad feels here.

19:55.795 --> 19:57.797
Aww.

19:57.830 --> 19:59.932
I'm glad Dora
didn't miss this.

19:59.966 --> 20:02.635
I still can't believe
Andy isn't missing this.

20:02.669 --> 20:05.305
Think you underestimated
both of them.

20:05.338 --> 20:08.007
And you.

20:08.040 --> 20:10.477
Thanks for holding my hand
while my kids are letting go.

20:10.510 --> 20:14.914
* Deep inside I hope
you'll feel it, too *

20:14.947 --> 20:17.717
Well, guess we should stop
creeping and head on home.

20:17.750 --> 20:18.718
Actually...

20:18.751 --> 20:21.721
I was thinking we could
do something else first.

20:21.754 --> 20:23.423
[ Chuckles ]

20:23.456 --> 20:25.625
Would you go to prom
with me?

20:25.658 --> 20:26.926
Oh, my God, prom.

20:26.959 --> 20:28.895
Yes, yes, yes,
yes, yes, yes, yes!

20:28.928 --> 20:32.365
* Who wants to be with you
* I'm the one, oh

20:32.399 --> 20:34.033
Okay.

20:34.066 --> 20:37.670
Well, is prom everything
you hoped it would be?

20:37.704 --> 20:39.339
Mm, it's perfect.

20:39.372 --> 20:43.576
Clara: Uh, Andy, is that
your dad and his girlfriend?

20:43.610 --> 20:45.278
My God,
have you no shame?!

20:45.312 --> 20:46.813
What is wrong
with you two?!

20:46.846 --> 20:48.948
Mary: 20-plus years
in the making,

20:48.981 --> 20:50.650
and we finally
got our prom, girl!

20:50.683 --> 20:53.386
Let's hit the limo
and make some mistakes!

20:53.420 --> 20:56.956
* To be with you

20:56.989 --> 20:58.391
* Ooh

21:01.461 --> 21:06.399
[ Crowd cheering ]

21:08.535 --> 21:10.002
* Yeah, you know what we about

21:10.036 --> 21:11.938
* Partying, like, so loud

21:11.971 --> 21:14.307
* Getting down,
like, all night, let's go *

21:14.341 --> 21:16.676
* Tonight we step it up...

21:16.709 --> 21:17.910
[ Crowd cheering ]

21:17.944 --> 21:20.713
* Step it up and fly away

21:20.747 --> 21:22.315
Oh, my God!

21:22.349 --> 21:24.751
* Got our heads up
in the clouds *

21:24.784 --> 21:26.519
* Oh, oh, oh
* Where tonight?

21:26.553 --> 21:28.555
* Where tonight?
Oh, oh, oh, where tonight? *
